{
  "stem": "22972.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And the BDJJ was an exact copy of the Hitler Youth.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "We marched, believe it or not.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "In 1935 we marched through the streets of Berlin with our blue and white flags with the Mogen David on it, and traffic didn't stop for us.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "But we marched.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Most of the time, we would go into quiet neighborhoods or to outskirts of Berlin, and we did our marching there.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "But we had song books, and instead of the Horst Wessel Lied, which was the-- the National Anthem of the Nazi party, we sang the Hatikvah.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And instead of 'Jewish blood will spurt,' [?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Juden Blud Musst Spritzen, ?] which was the main battle cry of the Hitler Youth, we said, 'Tomorrow in Jerusalem.' I became very, very religious.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "I went to temple every single Friday night, every Saturday, every holiday.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "I went to Dr.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Joachim Prinz's temple, which was in West Berlin, close to my home.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And then I was afforded a great, great honor.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "I was allowed to go to a meeting of all of the big shots of the BDJJ that had been brought to Berlin from all over Germany.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And before I passed out on the stage, after listening to three hours of speeches-- and I wasn't the only one that passed out-- I was listening to all the speeches and I thought to myself, my God, what they're really doing is they're copying Hitler.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And this is ridiculous.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "We shouldn't be copying Hitler.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "We should be doing our own thing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And I resigned from the Bund the next day and never went back again.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "But it was a very, very intense Jewish period in my life.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "I started wearing dresses again and led a more normal life.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't think it had much effect.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
